Sorry.

00:42:26.050 --> 00:42:30.980
She's a researcher in
the marine bioacoustics

00:42:30.980 --> 00:42:35.120
lab at Scripps, and
in particular focusing

00:42:35.120 --> 00:42:39.550
on marine bioacoustics,
and in particular

00:42:39.550 --> 00:42:43.680
of exploited marine mammals,
which I take to mean

00:42:43.680 --> 00:42:47.300
whales and that sort of thing.

00:42:47.300 --> 00:42:50.190
So I don't know why,
but I have to come up

00:42:50.190 --> 00:42:52.472
with some anecdote for
each talk or at least

00:42:52.472 --> 00:42:53.680
something that fascinated me.

00:42:53.680 --> 00:42:58.260
And I guess, although
I knew that whales talk

00:42:58.260 --> 00:43:03.580
to each other I grew up hearing
about songs of humpback whales,

00:43:03.580 --> 00:43:06.230
I only recently heard an
anecdote which I really

00:43:06.230 --> 00:43:07.150
have to track down.

00:43:07.150 --> 00:43:11.960
I have to try this that
evidently Inouit, a group

00:43:11.960 --> 00:43:16.850
of Inouit in what used to be
the Northwest Territories, which

00:43:16.850 --> 00:43:22.600
guess in now the Netsilik
Territory in Canada,

00:43:22.600 --> 00:43:25.050
they would hunt whales.

00:43:25.050 --> 00:43:26.740
The way they would
find whales is

00:43:26.740 --> 00:43:29.680
to take a paddle,
their kayak paddle,

00:43:29.680 --> 00:43:33.030
and put it in the water put
their ear next to the paddle

00:43:33.030 --> 00:43:35.260
blade, and they
could actually hear

00:43:35.260 --> 00:43:36.862
when the whales were close by.

00:43:36.862 --> 00:43:39.070
And that would be how they
would know they were close

00:43:39.070 --> 00:43:40.900
and they could actually
go on the hunt.

00:43:40.900 --> 00:43:43.900
So apparently
bioacoustics has been

00:43:43.900 --> 00:43:47.430
known to humans for
years and years,

00:43:47.430 --> 00:43:51.060
but it's now being
used to understand them

00:43:51.060 --> 00:43:56.530
and unfortunately, one of
the byproducts of humans

00:43:56.530 --> 00:43:59.090
is to pollute just
about everything

00:43:59.090 --> 00:44:00.560
we can get our hands on.

00:44:00.560 --> 00:44:02.590
So we have light
pollution in the sky

00:44:02.590 --> 00:44:04.650
and we have noise
pollution in the oceans.

00:44:04.650 --> 00:44:08.050
So anyway, Anna.

